title: 207 - Tent Maker
description:
Two things that ETA organization embody is accountability and self-awareness. Your ability to be honest about yourself and your situation is the foundation to changing your life. Today on the podcast the guys discuss how your inability to self-assess can keep you in denial and stuck.
 Denial is a pain killer and blaming others can and will keep you in the same position that you’re complaining about. Be prepared for a reality check on today’s show to see how aware you are.
 The Secret to Success Topics:
  [06:15] - Get Humbled
 [10:00] - Fair or Foul
 [22:00] - Denial 
 [38:00] - Rage
 [52:00] - Hold Me Accountable
 [1:03:00] - Get Around the Right People

 Study when it’s convenient for you and take your mobile classroom wherever you go. Earn a quality online degree at an accredited college and enjoy all the benefits of the Ashford experience:   www.Ashford.edu/success

  Secrets of the 1%:
  Denial is a pain killer.
 Your ego will keep you in the same position.
 Take inventory of who you really are versus who people think you are.
